      "sql": "WITH dated AS (\n  SELECT id, event_date,\n         strftime('%w', event_date) AS wday\n  FROM events\n)\nSELECT id, event_date, wday\nFROM dated\nWHERE wday IN ('0', '6')\nORDER BY event_date;",
      "explanation": "1. The CTE `dated` computes `wday` once for every row ÔÇö the `strftime` call lives in a single place.\n2. The outer query filters on the already-computed `wday` column using `IN ('0', '6')`, making the intent clearer and avoiding repeating the expression.\n3. This pattern ÔÇö compute derived columns in a CTE, filter on them in the outer query ÔÇö scales well when multiple downstream filters or projections need the same computed value."
